    <weatherForecast/>
    <avalancheActivity>
      <highlights>The danger of moist and wet avalanches will already increase in the late morning.</highlights>
      <comment>Rise of the zero-degree level up to 3400 m. &lt;br/> &lt;br/> The early morning will see favourable conditions, but the danger of wet and gliding avalanches will increase later. &lt;br/> As a consequence of warming during the day and solar radiation the avalanche prone locations will become more prevalent from the late morning. These conditions will cause a rapid weakening of the snowpack in particular on steep sunny slopes. Medium-sized natural avalanches are possible here. Increase in danger of moist and wet snow slides in particular in steep rocky terrain. &lt;br/> &lt;br/> Backcountry tours and off-piste skiing should be started and concluded very early. &lt;br/> &lt;br/> Especially on very steep northwest, north and northeast facing slopes avalanches can be triggered in the weakly bonded old snow. This applies in particular in case of a large load.</comment>
    </avalancheActivity>
    <snowpackStructure>
      <comment>The surface of the snowpack will freeze to form a strong crust only at high altitudes and will soften earlier than the day before. &lt;br/> &lt;br/> Especially steep shady slopes high altitudes: Individual weak layers exist in the centre of the snowpack. &lt;br/> &lt;br/> At elevated altitudes snow depths vary greatly, depending on the infuence of the wind. &lt;br/> In general, snow conditions in many regions are still good and are in line with or above the seasonal average. At low altitude and on sunny slopes the snowpack will soften quickly.</comment>
    </snowpackStructure>
